\par 
\par KNOWN ISSUES
\par 
\par dbExpress 
\par 
\par * After installing this update, the dbxdrivers.ini file will not
\par   contain an entry for MSSQL=1. If you require that entry, edit
\par   the ini file manually after installing the update. By default,
\par   dbxdrivers.ini is located at C:\\Program Files\\Common
\par   Files\\Borland Shared\\DBExpress.
\par   
\par * When installing this update, the existing registry values for
\par   the dbExpress connection and driver registry files
\par   (dbxconnections.ini and dbxdrivers.ini) are overwritten with
\par   the default location (C:\\Program Files\\Common Files\\Borland
\par   Shared\\DBExpress) if the "Common Files" directory is installed
\par   on a different, non-default drive. This causes a
\par   "Driver/Connection Registry File 'C:\\Program Files\\Common
\par   Files\\Borland Shared\\DBExpress\\dbx....' not found" error at
\par   design time when Delphi attempts to locate one of these files.
\par  
\par   To resolve this issue, perform the following steps after
\par   installing this update:
\par    
\par   1. Shutdown Delphi 7. 
\par   
\par   2. Modify the registry key value
\par      'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Borland\\DBExpress\\Connection
\par      Registry File' to reflect the actual location of your
\par      dbxconnections.ini file (see the warning below).  
\par   
\par   3. Modify the registry key value
\par      'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Borland\\DBExpress\\Driver
\par      Registry File'  to reflect the actual location of your
\par      dbxdrivers.ini file.
\par      
\par   WARNING ABOUT EDITING THE REGISTRY
\par  
\par   Perform Windows registry edits at your own risk.  The registry
\par   is a critical component of your operating system, and any
\par   mistakes made while editing it can cause your machine to stop
\par   functioning. This document and  other product documentation
\par   describes how to edit your registry. In most cases, Borland
\par   recommends using the Microsoft Regedit tool to perform
\par   editing. Whatever tool you use, however, you should, before
\par   making any edits, make backups of your registry and thoroughly
\par   familiarize yourself with the editing tool and the registry
\par   editing process.
\par    
\par Unofficial Patches 
\par 
\par * If you have updated any Borland packages in the system32
\par   directory with unofficial patches or updates from CodeCentral,
\par   MSI might revert (auto-repair) those packages to their
\par   previous version during installation of this update.
\par   Therefore, after installing this update, you may need to 
\par   re-install unofficial patches or updates.
\par   
\par Empty Help Index Tab
\par 
\par * Due to a Windows Help engine limitation on Windows 98 and
\par   Millennium, the Help system Index tab will be empty if the
\par   index exceeds 32,767 keywords. 
\par   
\par   If you encounter an empty Help Index tab after installing this
\par   update, open the d7.ohi file in the Delphi7\\Help folder and
\par   comment out one or more of the index entries by changing the
\par   colon in column one to a semi-colon, as shown here:
\par   
\par   ;Index Open Tools API (IOTA)=d7iota.hlp
\par 
\par   Save the d7.ohi file and delete any hidden *.GID files in your
\par   Delphi7/Help folder before restarting the Help.  
\par   
\par   This modification reduces the number of index keywords, but
\par   does not affect other Help system functionality, such as
\par   cross-file linking or F1 accessibility.
\par   
