\par 
\par ISSUES ADDRESSED BY THIS UPDATE
\par 
\par This readme lists the maintenance for all editions of Delphi 7;
\par not all of the features mentioned in this file are available in
\par all editions of the product.
\par 
\par This update resolves the following issues:
\par 
\par IDE
\par 
\par * Using the up/down arrow keys to navigate and select items from
\par   the Code Completion window sometimes skips items (Quality
\par   Central 2875).
\par   
\par * In the Project Manager, units are incorrectly displayed in the
\par   order that they are listed in the USES clause, rather than
\par   alphabetically.
\par   
\par * Using collections containing component references and form
\par   inheritance can result in incorrect references being stored in
\par   the dfm file.
\par 
\par =======================================================
\par   
\par CORE DATABASE
\par 
\par * TFMTBCDField initializes to size 8 instead of size 4, allowing 
\par   the system to initialize precision to 7 and size to 8 
\par   (Quality Central 5938).
\par   
\par * Using a TDBLookupComboBox to display a list of data given
\par   by a detail TQuery results in the error "Field '' not found"
\par   (Quality Central 5384 and 4823).
\par   
\par * TDBRadioGroup maintains its focus on the most recently
\par   selected item, even after an edit has been canceled
\par   (Quality Central 2109).
\par   
\par * When using persistent TStringField objects, if the Size
\par   property is set to a value larger than the database column it
\par   references, data in neighboring fields may be overwritten
\par   (Quality Central 3974).  To prevent this, the Size property is
\par   now automatically reset to match the underlying database
\par   column size when the dataset is opened. This reset will occur
\par   at either design time or runtime, but it does not affect 
\par   read-only fields.
\par 
\par =======================================================
\par 
