\par   delta dataset still contains a record.  This happens if you
\par   populate the Nested Dataset field before populating another
\par   field that precedes it in the field order.
\par   
\par * The TClientDataSet.ApplyUpdates method fails if the dataset 
\par   contains only changes to fields that have the 
\par   ProviderFlags.pfnUpdate property set to False 
\par   (Quality Central 2338).
\par   
\par * TClientDataSet does not order correctly on a TLargeIntField 
\par   when used in an index or in the IndexFieldNames property 
\par   (Quality Central 1050 & 2626)
\par   
\par * TAggregateField returns an incorrect value after a 
\par   filter was used and then cleared (Quality Central 1712).
\par  
\par * A "Key violation" exception may incorrectly be generated
\par   when using poFetchDetailsOnDemand with a nested dataset that
\par   also has an InternalCalc field (Quality Central 2011).
\par   
\par * TClientDataSet may contain invalid Delta entries when using 
\par   poPropogateChanges. (Quality Central 2019 & 2333).
\par   
\par * Editing the value of an InternalCalc field on a nested 
