\par   
\par * Incorrect filter expression parsing occurs when parsing a
\par   value that contains a quote in TClientDataSet. The expression
\par   parser incorrectly treats the rest of the expression as a
\par   formula (Quality Central 1266). 
\par   
\par * TClientDataSet.ChangeCount will return an incorrect value 
\par   when editing the value of a TStringField or a 
\par   TWideStringField and then reverting it to the original value 
\par   (Quality Central 2717 & 4508).
\par   
\par * Canceling an update to an individual field by assigning the
\par   "unassigned" (varEmpty) value to TField.NewValue in the
\par   TDataSetProvider.BeforeUpdateRecord event handler does not
\par   work (Quality Central 3660).
\par   
\par * TClientDataset InternalCalc fields are reset to null after 
\par   calling the ApplyUpdates method when using 
\par   poPropogateChanges (Quality Central  3777).
\par   
\par * When using incremental fetching on a TClientDataset with 
\par   parameters, the associated TDatasetProvider will repeatedly 
\par   return the same set of records (Quality Central 3515).
\par   
\par * TClientDataset.FindKey will fail with an list index error
\par   when used on a cloned nested dataset (Quality Central 3786).
\par   
\par * When the size of a Persistent field in TClientDataSet is set
